Heat the oil in a pan over a medium heat. Add the onion and garlic and fry for 2-3 minutes to soften.Add the chicken pieces and fry for 3-4 minutes until they start to colour, then add the sweetcorn, mangetout and pepper, frying for a further 2-3 minutes.Add the stock, and leave to simmer on a medium heat for 8-10 minutes, until everything is cooked through and the liquid has slightly reduced.To serve, ladle into a bowl and eat piping hot with bread.